juniDs1MIB.name: juniDs1MIB

revisions.description: Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added support for FDL transmit mode, remote FDL strings and far end FDL carrier.
Updated version of this MIB module.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniDs1MIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniDs1MIB.description: The DS1/E1 MIB for the Juniper enterprise. This MIB contains managed objects to supplement those found in RFC1406 DS1/E1 MIB.

juniDsx1ConfigTable.name: juniDsx1ConfigTable
juniDsx1ConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for DS1/E1 interfaces present in the system.

juniDsx1ConfigEntry.name: juniDsx1ConfigEntry
juniDsx1ConfigEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an DS1/E1 interface.

juniDsx1TimeSlotMap.name: juniDsx1TimeSlotMap
juniDsx1TimeSlotMap.description: A bitmap representing the timeslots on the DS1/E1 interface that have been allocated for service. For channelized DS1/E1, set bits reflect the union of timeslot allocations across all fractional arrangements operating over this DS1/E1 interface. For unchannelized DS1/E1, all relevant timeslot bits will be set.

juniDsx1Ds1ChannelNumber.name: juniDsx1Ds1ChannelNumber
juniDsx1Ds1ChannelNumber.description: This variable represents the channel number of the DS1/E1 on its parent DS3/E3. A value of 0 indicates this DS1/E1 does not have a parent DS3/E3.

juniDsx1Capabilities.name: juniDsx1Capabilities
juniDsx1Capabilities.description: A value which indicates the set of capabilities of the DS1/E1 interface. The value is a sum. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each capability, C, in the range 1 through 3, that this interface supports, 2 raised to (C - 1) is added to the sum. For example, an interface which is only E1 capable would have a value of 2 (2^(2-1)). In contrast, an interface which is both T1 and J1 capable would have a value of 5 (2^(1-1) + 2^(3-1)). The values for DS1/E1 interface capabilities are as follows: capability function 1 T1 2 E1 3 J1

juniDsx1Mode.name: juniDsx1Mode
juniDsx1Mode.description: This variable represents the DS1/E1 interface mode. The value of the juniDsx1Capabilities object for the DS1/E1 interface indicates the valid set of values for this object.

juniDsx1LineBuildOutCapabilities.name: juniDsx1LineBuildOutCapabilities
juniDsx1LineBuildOutCapabilities.description: A value which indicates the set of line build out capabilities of the DS1/E1 interface. The value is a sum. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each line build out capability, C, in the range 1 or 2, that this interface supports, 2 raised to (C - 1) is added to the sum. For example, an interface which is only short haul capable would have a value of 2 (2^(2-1)). In contrast, an interface which is both short haul and long haul capable would have a value of 3 (2^(1-1) + 2^(2-1)). The values for DS1/E1 interface line build out capabilities are as follows: line build out capability function 1 short haul 2 long haul

juniDsx1LineBuildOutType.name: juniDsx1LineBuildOutType
juniDsx1LineBuildOutType.description: This variable represents the configured line build out type of the DS1/E1 interface. The value of the juniDsx1LineBuildOutCapabilities object for the DS1/E1 interface indicates the valid set of values for this object.

juniDsx1LineAttenuation.name: juniDsx1LineAttenuation
juniDsx1LineAttenuation.description: This variable represents the configured line attenuation of the DS1/E1 interface. Note that the value of this object only takes effect when the value of the juniDsx1LineBuildOutType for the DS1/E1 interface is set to longHaul(2).

juniDsx1LineLength.name: juniDsx1LineLength
juniDsx1LineLength.description: This variable represents the length of the DS1/E1 line in meters. Note that the value of this object only takes effect when the value of the juniDsx1LineBuildOutType for the DS1/E1 interface is set to shortHaul(1).

juniDsx1LowerIfIndex.name: juniDsx1LowerIfIndex
juniDsx1LowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface over which this Dsx1 interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

juniDsx1RowStatus.name: juniDsx1RowStatus
juniDsx1RowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniDsx1RowStatus juniDsx1LowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for ifIndex must have been determined previously, by reading juniDsx1NextIfIndex. The interface identified by juniDsx1hLowerIfIndex must exist. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created/ destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniDsx1SendCode.name: juniDsx1SendCode
juniDsx1SendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS1 interface by the device.

juniDsx1YellowAlarm.name: juniDsx1YellowAlarm
juniDsx1YellowAlarm.description: This bitmap indicates the yellow alarm settings, and is the sum of the capabilities.

juniDsx1RemoteLoopback.name: juniDsx1RemoteLoopback
juniDsx1RemoteLoopback.description: This variable indicates the remote loopback setting.

juniDsx1FdlCarrier.name: juniDsx1FdlCarrier
juniDsx1FdlCarrier.description: Specifies the interface is used in carrier environment.

juniDsx1FdlEic.name: juniDsx1FdlEic
juniDsx1FdlEic.description: This is the equipment identification code.

juniDsx1FdlLic.name: juniDsx1FdlLic
juniDsx1FdlLic.description: This is the location identification code.

juniDsx1FdlFic.name: juniDsx1FdlFic
juniDsx1FdlFic.description: This is the frame identification code.

juniDsx1FdlUnit.name: juniDsx1FdlUnit
juniDsx1FdlUnit.description: This is the unit identification code.

juniDsx1FdlPfi.name: juniDsx1FdlPfi
juniDsx1FdlPfi.description: This is the facility identification code.

juniDsx1FdlPort.name: juniDsx1FdlPort
juniDsx1FdlPort.description: This is the equipment port number.

juniDsx1FdlTransmit.name: juniDsx1FdlTransmit
juniDsx1FdlTransmit.description: Specifies transmission enabling. path - Bit 0 for path transmit. When this bit is set indicates path transmit is enabled; otherwise path transmit disabled. idlesignal - Bit 1 for idlesignal transmit. When this bit is set idlesingal transmit is enabled; otherwise idlesignal transmit disabled. testsignal - Bit 2 for testsignal transmit. When this bit is set testsignal transmit is enabled; otherwise testsignal transmit disabled. The value of this object defaults to zero, indicating that none of FDL transmit methods are enabled.

juniDs1NextIfIndex.name: juniDs1NextIfIndex
juniDs1NextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in juniDsx1ConfigTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniDsx1FarEndConfigTable.name: juniDsx1FarEndConfigTable
juniDsx1FarEndConfigTable.description: The DS1 Far End Configuration table.

juniDsx1FarEndConfigEntry.name: juniDsx1FarEndConfigEntry
juniDsx1FarEndConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Far End Configuration table.

juniDsx1FarEndLineIndex.name: juniDsx1FarEndLineIndex
juniDsx1FarEndLineIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the DS1 interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value a dsx1LineIndex object instance.

juniDsx1FarEndEquipCode.name: juniDsx1FarEndEquipCode
juniDsx1FarEndEquipCode.description: This is the Far End Equipment Identification code that describes the specific piece of equipment. It is sent within the Path Identification Message.

juniDsx1FarEndLocationIDCode.name: juniDsx1FarEndLocationIDCode
juniDsx1FarEndLocationIDCode.description: This is the Far End Location Identification code that describes the specific location of the equipment. It is sent within the Path Identification Message.

juniDsx1FarEndFrameIDCode.name: juniDsx1FarEndFrameIDCode
juniDsx1FarEndFrameIDCode.description: This is the Far End Frame Identification code that identifies where the equipment is located within a building at a given location. It is sent within the Path Identification Message.

juniDsx1FarEndUnitCode.name: juniDsx1FarEndUnitCode
juniDsx1FarEndUnitCode.description: This is the Far End code that identifies the equipment location within a bay. It is sent within the Path Identification Message.

juniDsx1FarEndFacilityIDCode.name: juniDsx1FarEndFacilityIDCode
juniDsx1FarEndFacilityIDCode.description: This code identifies a specific Far End DS1 path. It is sent within the Path Identification Message.

juniDsx1FarEndPortNumber.name: juniDsx1FarEndPortNumber
juniDsx1FarEndPortNumber.description: This code identifies the port number of the Far End DS1. It is sent within the Idle Signal Message.

juniDsx1FarEndGeneratorNumber.name: juniDsx1FarEndGeneratorNumber
juniDsx1FarEndGeneratorNumber.description: This code identifies the Far End DS1 Generator Number. It is sent within the Test Signal Message.

juniDsx1FarEndCarrier.name: juniDsx1FarEndCarrier
juniDsx1FarEndCarrier.description: Specifies the interface is used in carrier environment. It is sent with all FDL messages.
